In [9]:
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

# we have 12 variables, so the maximum number of principal components has to be 12
nb_components = 3
pca = PCA(n_components = nb_components)
pca.fit(data_scaled)
data_pca = pca.transform(data_scaled)
In [10]:

annot_kws={"size":10}, yticklabels=colnames, vmax=1, vmin=-1, center=0)

In [12]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
import numpy as np
X=np.array(list(zip(data_pca[:,0],data_pca[:,1])))
colors= ['b','g','c','k']
markers= ['o','v','h','+']
plt.ylabel('PCA dimension')

kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3).fit(X)
plt.scatter(kmeans.cluster_centers_[:,0],kmeans.cluster_centers_[:,1],s=200,c='red',label='Centroids')

for i, l in enumerate(kmeans.labels_):
    plt.plot(data_pca[:,0][i],data_pca[:,1][i],color=colors[l],marker=markers[l])
plt.xlabel(' PCA dimension ')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
In [13]:
ssd = []
range_n_clusters = [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]
for num_clusters in range_n_clusters:
    kkmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=num_clusters, max_iter=1000)
    kkmeans.fit(X)
    
    ssd.append(kkmeans.inertia_)

plt.plot(ssd)
